    <article class="article PageDW-enJavaScriptReferenceGlobalObjectsNumberToLocaleString" role="main"><div class="page-title hideforedit">&#13;
              <h1 class="first entry-title roundTop" id="title">Number.ToLocaleString</h1>            &#13;
      &#13;
              </div>&#13;
      &#13;
    <div class="page-content boxed">&#13;
&#13;
     &#13;
       &#13;
    &#13;
            &#13;
      <div id="page-top"><div class="pageText" id="pageText">
<p>This method available to numbers will convert the number into a string which is suitable for presentation in the given locale.</p>
<table class="standard-table"><thead><tr><th colspan="2" class="header">Method of <a title="en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number" rel="internal" href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number"><code>Number</code></a></th> </tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Implemented in</td> <td>JavaScript ?</td> </tr><tr><td>ECMAScript Edition</td> <td>ECMAScript ? Edition</td> </tr></tbody></table><div id="section_1"><span id="Syntax"/><h3 class="editable">Syntax</h3>
<p><code><em>number</em>.toLocaleString()</code></p>
</div><div id="section_2"><span id="Examples"/><h3 class="editable">Examples</h3>
&#13;
          <pre name="code" class="js">var number = 3500
console.log(number.toLocaleString()); /* Displays "3,500" in English locale */</pre>&#13;
        
</div><div id="section_3"><span id="See_Also"/><h3 class="editable">See Also</h3>
<p><a title="en/Core_JavaScript_1.5_Reference/Global_Objects/Number/toString" rel="internal" href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Number/toString">Number.toString()</a></p></div></div></div>&#13;
